 as unfamiliar ways to exist and to leverage change. In doing so, Berger offers us a different nineteenth century—pushing our imaginative and critical thinking toward new terrain.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aAmerican literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLiberalism in literature. 0aLiberalismzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aLiterature and societyzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aPolitics and literaturezUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aSocial change in literature. 4aAmerican Studies. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh  aHarriet Beecher Stowe.  aHenry David Thoreau.  aMargaret Fuller.  aMartin Delany.  aNineteenth-century American literature.  aRalph Waldo Emerson.  aWilliam Wells Brown.  aantebellum U.S.  aecology.  aliberalism.  aneoliberalism.  aontology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020 Englishz978311070476108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020z9783110704563oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311072271040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823287772zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823287772423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823287772/original  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070476-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-072271-0  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-